rationale: The 'version' field in the PAS schema has no corresponding match in the Histology schema.
The 'donor_id' field in the PAS schema has no corresponding match in the Histology schema.
Both fields represent the ID of the tissue or sample from which the assay data originates.
No matching field found in the Histology schema for execution date and time.

Both fields refer to the DOI for protocols.io, though 'protocols_io_doi' in PAS refers to the protocol for the overall assay, while 'preparation_protocol_doi' in Histology is specific to sample preparation.
No corresponding field for the person executing the assay in the target schema.
No corresponding field for the operator's email in the target schema.
No corresponding field for the principal investigator in the target schema.
No corresponding field for the principal investigator's email in the target schema.
No match found for the 'assay_category' field in the Histology schema.
Both fields describe the specific type of assay or dataset being produced.
Both fields refer to the class of analytes measured in the assay.
Both fields specify whether the assay targets specific molecules.
Both fields describe the vendor of the instrument used in the assay.
Both fields refer to the specific model of the instrument used in the assay.

No corresponding field found in the Histology schema for pixel resolution unit (x).
No corresponding field found in the Histology schema for pixel resolution (y).
No corresponding field found in the Histology schema for pixel resolution unit (y).
No corresponding field found in the Histology schema for resolution in the z-axis.
No corresponding field found in the Histology schema for resolution unit in the z-axis.
Both fields describe the chemical stains used on the sample.
